赛 (sài): to compete / competition / match / to surpass / better than / superior to / to excel
比赛 (bǐsài): competition (sports etc) / match / CL: 場｜场, 次 / to compete
赛车 (sàichē): auto race / cycle race / race car
赛事 (sàishì): competition (e.g. sporting)
赛场 (sàichǎng): racetrack / field (for athletics competition)
参赛 (cānsài): to compete / to take part in a competition
开赛 (kāisài): to start a match / the kick-off
赛道 (sàidào): race course
公开赛 (gōngkāisài): (sports) open championship / open (as in "the US Open")
赛跑 (sàipǎo): race (running) / to race (running)
比赛场 (bǐsàichǎng): stadium / playing field for a competition
热身赛 (rèshēnsài): exhibition game
加时赛 (jiāshísài): (sports) overtime / extra time / play-off
赛车手 (sàichēshǒu): racing driver
赛车场 (sàichēchǎng): motor racetrack / cycle racetrack
表演赛 (biǎoyǎnsài): exhibition match
自行车赛 (zìxíngchēsài): cycle race
公路赛 (gōnglùsài): road race
赛会 (sàihuì): religious procession / exposition
百米赛跑 (bǎimǐsàipǎo): 100-meter dash
赛先生 ( Sàixiānsheng): "Mr Science", phrase used during the May 4th Movement 五四運動｜五四运动 / abbr. for 賽因斯｜赛因斯 / see also 德先生
加赛 (jiāsài): a play-off / replay
赛车场赛 (sàichēchǎngsài): stadium cycle race
出赛 (chūsài): to compete / to take part (in a sports event)
